Port Mapping :

$ docker run -it --rm -d -p 8080:80 --name web nginx







++++++
FLAGS:
+++++

-rm flag is there to tell the Docker Daemon to clean up the container and remove the file system after the container exits



-d 
Instead of running docker container with an interactive shell it is also possible to let docker container to run as a daemon
which means that the docker container would run in the background completely detached from your current shell
